			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Aamen wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">umm no if ya go oom / lom,  ya playing ya class to it fullest.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Of course every situation, group, raid etc calls for differing tactics. However.. there is one thing I usally do 95% of the time. Sit my mana and camp it around 40-50% mark. I am only FT 3 and by no means "uber" so I have to balance my nukes to my mana regen capability and pulling speed of the group.
<br />

<br />
Magi have a duty to keep something in reserve in case the pullers, pull a little more than the melees can manage. Think of the Marines in Cuba. Last line of defense. They walk the line. If you are a magi with no mana... your like a marine with no bullets when all hell breaks loose.
<br />

<br />
However... I expect when hell breaks loose for those bullets/mana to start to fly ASAP. And for those frikking Rangers (Both Army and EQ kind) not to pull any more if we low on mana/bullets.
<br />

<br />
So to take it back to EQ... yes you will on occasion go OOM... however... usally when I go out of mana... people die.
<br />

<br />
However... I like I said before... it is highly situational.
<br />

<br />
