				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I realize the original poster was looking at the  level 45 range, but this is something I wanted to add for 'down the road'
<br />

<br />
At 65, with about 50 aa, I find myself going petless more and more often.  In fast pull situations, such as BoT and Ssra, with a knight that can agro lock its just more efficient to nuke - nuke - cani - cani - rain - cani..... I've set up my gear (Summoning Haste 4, Mana Pres 4, Pet focus), AAs (Quick Summon 1, SCM 3), and Spec (Conjuration) to maximize pet cani.  1 round gives me 225 mana on avg, and takes about 8 sec (about 170 a tick).  In the time it would take to suspend pet and then unsuspend and /pet attack, I could have cani more and nuke enough to outdamage the pet.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I've usually got an equiped buffed pet in cold storage, just in case.   But it feels as though poor jobober is becoming obsolete.  Though, it is fun to be able to out nuke a wizzy due to sheer strength of mana regen.<br />_________________<br />Atlane
<br />
65th Mage</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
