			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Bottom line, just like any class in your game.  If you sit around, sucking your thumb, you'll be worthless.  If you actively and visibly work your ass off every time you get into a group, you'll get more groups.
<br />

<br />
Work it, baby, for every thing you got.  You don't need to go OOM to do it, but you are the Guardian!
<br />

<br />
If EQ were a soccer match, you would be a half back.  Helping the forwards take it home, but protecting your own just as much.  You run the most, spend the most energy, and have to be constantly vigilant.  Mages are one of the few classes can fill more roles than any other class.  And what you do before the pull matters just as much if not more than what you do during battle.
<br />

<br />
WE RULE!  Go MAGES!<br />_________________<br />Rylden Riptide - Rodcet Nife
<br />

<br />
"The most painful state of being is remembering the future." - Kierkegaard</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
