			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I stay at 80% mana when xping. I have FT15 also, but I stayed at 80 even before Ft was in game.
<br />

<br />
Basically it allows me to have a constant supply of mana that won't regen to full unless the group sucks. If one of my damage aa's pop (HoE, SoR etc..) then i burn myself to 70% and sit through the next mob and let me aa's do the mana free damage along with the ept while I med back up to 80.  If something goes terribly wrong where mobs can't be mez'd fro whatever reason, i normally offtank one of them myself and let the ept tank another one. I have all the spell casting aa's that help cast through being hit, so normally i just keep nuking. Normally the mobs are slowed and i can normally burn them down before they get me down. I also have SoA if I need to use the rune.
<br />

<br />
But yeah, always stay at a certain ammount of mana, determined by YOU. Don't go OOm unless there is an emergency as it's jyust not needed. Pace yourself, sit down to med during fights if you need to to keep yourself at that predetermined set amount of mana.
<br />

<br />
Unless it's clsoe to the end of adventure and you wanna hurry it up...then feel free to nuke to oom =P</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
