			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The Key is to maximise the use of your mana
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">umm no if ya go oom / lom, ya playing ya class to it fullest, </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Nothing bugs me more when I play my main (Shaman) than to be in a group where 1 DPS class chain nukes the first few mobs, melee take very little damage, cleric is at 90% mana, and we then have to wait while said DPS regains mana, or fight inefficiently with insufficient DPS.  Playing your class to the fullest is maintaining a balance between mana usage and mana regen that serves your group the best.  If any one member of your group is OOM then the group is not being efficient.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">* Most importantly, maintain a significant mana pool to be able to burn down multiple mobs when things go wrong </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This cannot be emphasised enough, the number of times I have seen a wipe avioded because the DPS in a group were wise enough to keep mana in reserve and were able to nuke the group out of trouble.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=756283" target="_blank" class="postlink">Perelicus</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
